{"key":"post-9497340","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9497340</id>\n<content>If you're making a mini-greenhouse, get a good analog hygrometer, and then use a good cycle timer to operate your humidifier.&amp;nbsp; I tried all the major brands of humidistats a few years ago, including the expensive ones, and none can stand up to the spore loads we get in mycology.&amp;nbsp;  Use timers to dial in your humidifiers and adjust them weekly or so as the ambient conditions change.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For terrariums, use perlite humidification and holes per the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;shotgun terrarium tek&lt;/a&gt;, and you'll be fine.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9500215</next>\n<prev>9497314</prev>\n<first>9496362</first>\n<last>9501784</last>\n<when>1230321670</when>\n<utime>12/26/08 10:01 PM</utime>\n</post>"}